    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-4122753">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-4122753">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4122753)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4122753">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="2303803"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1547806540 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 Jan 2019 10:15</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4122753">
									

<p>What MMG said. This is just your headcanon. I get equally frustrated when I see the opposite (abusive Foundation) because it's not what I like, just like this isn't what you like. And honestly, it's not just that I don't like it, it's that it doesn't make sense to me, for all the reasons MMG said and all the reasons I had the Committee give in this article.</p>
<p>So do you think that in psychiatric hospitals and rehab programs IRL, patients get called a number and experiemented on without their consent? No? That would be nuts because ~it's real life~, right? Well, could it be because the people holding them know they're not criminals and deserve to be treated with at least a little respect, because they don't even want to be there and don't objectively 'deserve' it?</p>
<p>Well, there you have it. SCPs are not inmates, they are closer to patients. The Foundation's job is &quot;secure, contain, protect&quot; and all of those things are possible even with a demeanor that isn't shitty. &quot;Research&quot; has never been a priority in the Foundation's mission, you know.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I'm starting to dislike this whole push for a progressive, diverse Foundation.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&#8230;Then again, if you're a user who thinks basic respectful treatment is <em>political</em> and especially ~progressive~, we may not get anywhere.</p>

							</div>

								
