														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4168849">
									

<p>While it's true the Foundation will always place the continued survival of humanity above all else, it seems like it'd be conductive to this goal to treat sapient skips well. It means they'll be less complaints about the foundation staff abusing anomalies for no good reason, avoiding possible budget cuts and making it harder to capture entities down the line. In addition to that, if the SCP feels &quot;at home&quot; it's more likely to comply with the Foundation</p>
<p>The Foundation staff is full of people who willingly sent prisoners to die agonizing deaths, they can probably call somebody by their name without compromising their ability to act cold and rational.</p>

